EXTRACTED VALUE: "Captain Roth will do that for you, won't you, Captain? While I put the baby down."
"Silence," her mother said gently. "Let him do his work, let God do His, and let me do mine." She closed her eyes in prayer.
We hit an air pocket and the plane drops, my stomach lurching.
Corcoran nodded, avoiding my eyes. I felt the first stirrings of uneasiness.
